{{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|October (Old Calendar)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=}}, the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|Senbu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[文治]] 1st year（[[Julian calendar]] [[1185]] [[November 11]]） – In the 1st year of the Bunji era, Emperor Go-Shirakawa issued an imperial decree ordering Minamoto no Yoshitsune to campaign against Minamoto no Yoritomo{{要出典|date=2021-03|qq=}}. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 11th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1568]] [[November 7]]） – Ashikaga Yoshiaki, supported by Oda Nobunaga, was installed as the 15th shogun of the Ashikaga Shogunate. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1870]] [[November 11]]） – Yataro Iwasaki founded Tsukumo Shokai, the precursor to Mitsubishi.
== Births == * {{ill|Bunroku|ja|Bunroku|qq=}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1595]] [[November 19]]） – Mōri Hidemasa, the 2nd lord of the Chōshū Domain (d. [[1651]]). * In the 3rd year of the Meiji era ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1870]] [[November 11]]） – Daisetsu Suzuki, a Buddhist thinker (d. [[1966]]).
== Deaths == * [[Keichō]] 7th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1602]] [[December 1]]） – Kobayakawa Hideaki, a military commander (born [[1582]]). * [[Keichō]] 15th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1610]] [[December 3]]） – Honda Tadakatsu, a daimyo and one of the Four Heavenly Kings of Tokugawa (born [[1548]]). * {{ill|Hōei|ja|Hōei|qq=}} 7th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1710]] [[December 8]]） – Tsugaru Nobumasa, lord of the Hirosaki Domain (born [[1646]]).
== See Also == {{Lunar Calendar See Also|10|17|10|19|9|18|11|10|1018|qq=}}
