{{Not to be confused with|October 18|qq=October 18}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月十八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 18일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|October (Old Calendar)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}, the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|Rokuyō|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|Senbu|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
== Events == * [[文治]] 1st year（[[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[November 11]]） – In the 1st year of the Bunji era, Emperor Go-Shirakawa issued an imperial decree ordering Minamoto no Yoshitsune to campaign against Minamoto no Yoritomo{{Citation needed|date=2021-03|qq=}}. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 11th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1568]] [[November 7]]） – Ashikaga Yoshiaki, supported by Oda Nobunaga, was installed as the 15th shogun of the Ashikaga Shogunate. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1870]] [[November 11]]） – Yataro Iwasaki founded Tsukumo Shokai, the precursor to Mitsubishi.
== Births == * {{ill|Bunroku|ja|Bunroku|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunroku|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1595]] [[November 19]]） – Mōri Hidemasa, the 2nd lord of the Chōshū Domain (d. [[1651]]). * In the 3rd year of the Meiji era ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1870]] [[November 11]]） – Daisetsu Suzuki, a Buddhist thinker (d. [[1966]]).
== Deaths == * [[Keichō]] 7th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1602]] [[December 1]]） – Kobayakawa Hideaki, a military commander (born [[1582]]). * [[Keichō]] 15th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1610]] [[December 3]]） – Honda Tadakatsu, a daimyo and one of the Four Heavenly Kings of Tokugawa (born [[:en:1548|1548]]). * {{ill|Hōei|ja|Hōei|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 7th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1710]] [[December 8]]） – Tsugaru Nobumasa, lord of the Hirosaki Domain (born [[1646]]).
